Another highly recommended book, especially if you love true life stories and some intense journeys (both physical and spiritual)! 

This book has a harrowing beginning made worse by the fact it's all true. But the positivity and perseverance that both Raynor and Moth is truly inspiring.

What I liked most about this book is that I knew a lot of the places described, as it's set along the South West coastal paths. Raynor Winn describes them so beautifully, it made me look at the world differently and reminded me not to take my good fortune for granted.

This book is also a commentary on UK homelessness (not what I was expecting)  and it's eye-opening how backwards UK laws are regarding people who are already suffering.

Give it a read, but be warned, like Raynor and Moth, you might be changed along the way.

